<div class="main1">
<p>Unless otherwise stated, textual material on the UB History web-site
may be reproduced freely, electronically or in print, provided:</p>
<ol type="1" class="x1">
<li>that full acknowledgement of the source is made</li>
<li>that the use is not for profit 
<small>(if you <em>do</em> want to use something in a
commercial publication, please contact the author)</small></li>
</ol> 
<p>"Full acknowledgment of the source" means that all of the following should
be given:</p>
<ul>
<li>the author of the page (if given)</li>
<li>the title of the page</li>
<li>the site</li>
<li>the URL</li>
</ul>
<p>For example, if you wish to reproduce Neil Parsons' 
Botswana History Page 13 (Society), something like the following
needs to appear:</p>
<p class="cite-example">(From Neil Parsons, 
<cite>Botswana History Pages (no. 13, Society)</cite>,
University of Botswana History Department web-site,
&lt;http://www.thuto.org/ubh/bw/bhp13.htm&gt;)</p>


<p>The copyright holder will normally be indicated at the end of each page.
In all cases, including where copyright is given as "University of 
Botswana History Department", the actual author reserves full rights to
reproduce or re-use his or her own material.</p>

<hr>
<p>For further discussion of the citation of electronic sources, see
<a href="web/cite.htm">our page on citation of electronic sources</a>.</p>
</div><!-- End "main1" -->

